Duane F. SPARKS et al., Appellants, v. McNEIL CONSTRUCTION CO., a Corporation, Appellee. No. 11333. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 24, 1946. Benjamin D. Brown, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Charles H. Carr, U. S. Atty., and Ronald Walker and Robert E. Wright, Asst. U. S. Atty., all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, for dismissal of appeal herein, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly and that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
